<p>U.S. Secretary of State Marco Rubio visited Israel on October 24–25 and urged a rapid assembly of an international force to police the fragile Gaza ceasefire that President Trump helped negotiate, saying such a mission could be put together quickly . Palestinian factions agreed that technocrats would administer Gaza after the war, according to statements reported during the talks . At the same time, U.S. reconnaissance flights over Gaza aim to provide independent monitoring of the truce, while aid deliveries remain well below needs amid border restrictions .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/8__CranreDU8odZUMGn1aT6R_9uVe8nf6cDkOLvB3FIuS4ThagfyRFDl_7vHroPbsmOmDhQDd5kIearBsBtbW2SEXHB9UBG3GvgtydsAVHBdHZ2mYExh-wN4_5zmm3kMGLCYN4-tFkIGtioqf057ul8pxzwx6hs2vT1LNBNmspoU_cgGmLRL3Jb-0tHvbfEpwSCxsx6nwNTYkBAABzAoacXvosgJIv9JBpBMLepVk60WmYXZnnXeTvSGNzl6ykGsXK9Xta8X7nnc' alt='US Secretary of State Marco Rubio speaks to the media after visiting the Civil-Military Coordination Center in southern Israel on October 24, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Mission makeup: Rubio said the proposed international mission could include up to a dozen nations and organisations and that Hamas would have no role in it .</li><li>Aid shortfall: Since the ceasefire began, fewer than 100 UN and partner trucks have entered Gaza daily—far below the 600-per-day figure President Trump’s plan envisaged .</li><li>Criticism on aid: Analysts argue Rubio’s public rejection of UNRWA reflects a partisan U.S. stance on Gaza aid that could complicate humanitarian coordination .</li><li>Multinational monitoring: Australia, France, Spain and the UAE have sent personnel to a new southern Israel centre coordinating ceasefire monitoring .</li><li>Independent oversight: U.S. drone flights over Gaza aim to verify conditions on the ground and supplement partner information about possible ceasefire violations .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. Secretary of State Marco Rubio / U.S. government: Rubio visited Israel and pressed for a quick multinational mission to enforce and monitor the ceasefire, stressing that Hamas would not be part of any enforcement role . (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/25/rubio-seeks-quick-deployment-of-international-force-to-police-ceasefire-in-gaza_6746759_4.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li><li>Palestinian factions: Palestinian factions agreed that a committee of technocrats would run Gaza after the war, according to a joint statement reported during negotiations . (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/gaza-us-seeks-quick-deployment-of-international-force/a-74491211'>Deutsche Welle</a>)</li><li>Aid organisations coalition: A coalition of 41 aid groups warned Israel’s rejection of many aid applications is blocking lifesaving supplies and urged easing restrictions to prevent more preventable deaths . (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/aid-groups-urge-israel-stop-blocking-gaza-aid'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Analyst Mouin Rabbani (Al Jazeera): Rabbani said Rubio’s campaign against UNRWA demonstrates a U.S. bias in how Washington is approaching Gaza aid and politics . (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/video/quotable/2025/10/25/rubios-crusade-against-unrwa-shows-us-bias-on-gaza-aid'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/25/rubio-seeks-quick-deployment-of-international-force-to-police-ceasefire-in-gaza_6746759_4.html'>Rubio seeks quick deployment of international force to police ceasefire in Gaza</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/video/quotable/2025/10/25/rubios-crusade-against-unrwa-shows-us-bias-on-gaza-aid'>Rubio’s “crusade” against UNRWA shows US bias on Gaza aid</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/gaza-us-seeks-quick-deployment-of-international-force/a-74491211'>Gaza: US seeks quick deployment of international force</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/video/rubio-calls